      "inheritance_hierarchy": "Core wallet logic is an implementation contract deployed behind a minimal delegatecall proxy (Wallet.creationCode). Stage1Module and Stage2Module are implementations. Both inherit: Calls (which inherits ReentrancyGuard, BaseAuth, Nonce) + Auth module (Stage1Auth or Stage2Auth) + Hooks + ERC4337v07. BaseAuth implements IAuth, IPartialAuth, ISapient, IERC1271, and SelfAuth. Implementation provides upgrade pointer management (onlySelf). SessionManager is a separate sapient signer contract (not part of the wallet implementation) inheriting ImplicitSessionManager and ExplicitSessionManager (which inherits PermissionValidator). Recovery and Passkeys are separate sapient signer contracts.",
      "external_dependencies": [
        "EVM precompile sha256 at address 0x02 (used by WebAuthn.verify via assembly staticcall)",
        "RIP-7212 P256 verifier precompile at 0x0000000000000000000000000000000000000100 (attempted by P256.verifySignature)",
        "Fallback Solidity P256 verifier contract at 0x000000000000D01eA45F9eFD5c54f037Fa57Ea1a (used by P256)",
        "ERC-4337 EntryPoint contract (IEntryPoint.depositTo; entrypoint-caller gating in ERC4337v07)",
        "Arbitrary external contracts called by wallet via Calls.execute/selfExecute and by Hooks fallback delegatecall",
        "ERC-1271 contracts used as signers (BaseSig/Recovery call IERC1271.isValidSignature)",
        "Sapient signer contracts used as signers (BaseSig calls ISapient/ISapientCompact; wallet accepts their imageHash contribution)"
      ],
      "upgrade_patterns": "Custom delegatecall proxy (Wallet.creationCode) stores implementation at storage slot keyed by the proxy's own address (sstore(address(), implementation)). Implementation updates are onlySelf, meaning upgrades must be executed via wallet self-call path (i.e., an authorized Calls.execute that calls updateImplementation on itself). Stage1Auth automatically upgrades the proxy to a fixed Stage2Module implementation when updateImageHash is called the first time. No OZ UUPS/Transparent beacon; no Diamond.",
      "access_control_structure": "No owner/roles. Control is signature-based: Calls.execute requires signatureValidation (BaseAuth) and nonce consumption; privileged management functions are onlySelf (must be invoked via self-call from wallet execution): setStaticSignature, updateImageHash, selfExecute, updateImplementation, addHook, removeHook. ERC-4337 entrypoint is immutable and enforced by msg.sender checks in validateUserOp/executeUserOp."
    },
